<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n26267d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26267d">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26267d"> 267(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ill. child = patresfamilias</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Institutions of the Private Law. The Law of the Family.]</font>&mdash;Both sons and daughters on emancipation ceased to be of the family of the <i>paterfamilias</i> who had emancipated them. A daughter&apos;s children could never as such be members of the family of their maternal grandfather; for children born in lawful marriage followed the family of their father, while <mark>those who were illegitimate ranked from the moment of birth as <i>patresfamilias</i></mark> and <i>matresfamilias</i>. <small> &ldquo;ROMAN LAW&rdquo; <a name="EBRL2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRL2"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 529</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
